Explanation

See also the bigrams and trigrams datasets.

We took the text of 262 language editions of Wikipedia and counted which letters appear how often. Next to the language name you find, sorted in order of how frequently they occur, the top 100 letters on that given Wikipedia. If you hoover over a letter, it will display you the percentage of the given letter in the given Wikipedia.

For some huge Wikipedias (de, en, es, fr, it, ja, nl, pl, ru) the numbers only represent part of the Wikipedia. The rest is left for control experiments.

The text was first cleaned by WikiExtractor, developed by Giuseppe Attardi and Antonio Fuschetto of the University of Pisa. We also provide, for comparison, a version of the not-cleaned data for unigrams and bigrams, inclduing language links, wiki syntax, template calls, and much more. We further removed some symbols from the above list (like brackets, punctuation, etc.).

You can download the complete unigram dataset (>2 MB).

The dumps used where the most recent ones as downloaded on October 9 2012.
